               <msContents>
                  <summary>Chants called Mäzǝmur, መጽሐፈ: መዝሙር:, with musical notation.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="1r" to="61r" facs="007">Fols 1r–61r</locus><title>Chants called Mäzǝmur, <foreign xml:lang="gez">መጽሐፈ: መዝሙር:</foreign></title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                     <note>with musical notation</note>

                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                     <locus target="#61r" facs="067">Fol. 61r</locus>
                       <q>“Glory to God who helped me to write this Mazmur, copied in the year of Mark the Evangelist when there is no epact and Mäṭǝqǝ‘. Its scribe is Mämhǝr Bäyänä. His city is Dälanta. His baptismal name is Gäbrä Maryam.”</q>
                     </colophon>

                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
